        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] Add Codex continuity bridge",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds the Codex Continuity Bridge to the bundled Codex plugin.\n\nThe bridge keeps Codex UI as the high-bandwidth workbench while giving OpenClaw a quiet operator surface for Telegram: status, recent threads, explicit watched completion checks, evidence-separated handoff briefs, and a gated write path that is disabled by default.\n\n## Safety Model\n\n- Read-only Codex app-server status is preferred.\n- SQLite fallback is read-only and explicitly stale-labeled.\n- Raw Codex app-server blobs are not exposed by the public HTTP routes.\n- Watch notifications are explicit, deduped, redacted, and quiet by default.\n- Telegram-to-Codex writes require an explicit feature flag plus provenance, trusted sender checks, repo allowlisting, risk gating, unambiguous target selection, and confirmed app-server write methods.\n- SQLite is never used as a write path.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm build`\n- `pnpm exec tsc -p extensions/codex/tsconfig.json --noEmit`\n- `pnpm exec vitest run extensions/codex/src/continuity/bridge.test.ts extensions/codex/src/commands.test.ts` (89 tests)\n- Local gateway smoke test for `/codex/status`, `/codex/threads`, `/codex/watch`, `/codex/watch/check`, `/codex/handoff`, and `/codex/goal`\n",
